### List users
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users

### Get one user
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/1

### Create user
POST http://localhost:8080/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{ "name": "Mia Brown", "email": "mia@example.com" }

### List products
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products

### Place an order — happy path
POST http://localhost:8080/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{ "userId": 1, "productId": 1, "quantity": 1 }

### Place an order — should 409 (insufficient stock)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{ "userId": 1, "productId": 1, "quantity": 99999 }

### Place an order — should 404 (no such user)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{ "userId": 9999, "productId": 1, "quantity": 1 }

### Place an order — should 400 (validation: quantity must be ≥ 1)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{ "userId": 1, "productId": 1, "quantity": 0 }

### List orders (with user + product joined)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/orders
